<br>
In order to get a task, walk up to a NPC and say &quot;task&quot; while they are targetted. I made a /macro called /whisper task, this does a say to just that NPC, prevents the Noob says, &quot;task&quot; spam.<br>
<br>
When you get a task, there are 3 kinds, a &quot;Kill Task&quot;, &quot;Fedex or Delivery Task&quot; and &quot;Consignment or Tradeskills Task&quot;. You have a set amount of time to complete the task, normally 120 real time minutes. This task will stay with you if you log out or zone. You will lose this task if you die or the time limit wears out.<br>
<br>
Fedex Task:<br>
You are given an item, and told to deliver it to an NPC. Directions on where this NPC is only offered when you were originally given the task. Very easy to do, the reward is some experience and some cash.<br>
<br>
NPC LIST: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://daoc.crgaming.com/npc">daoc.crgaming.com/npc</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Kill Task:<br>
You are given a mob to kill. When you kill the mob, you must come back to whoever gave you the task for your reward. The mob is normally blue or yellow. Almost always blue, if you search hard enough. These give the more experience and cash then Fedex Tasks (I'm guessing roughly 150% from memory).<br>
<br>
Consignment Tasks:<br>
This is a special task, made to develop tradeskills. You only get this task from your tradeskills master. You are given an item to make for an NPC. You must make the item, and then deliver it to an NPC. The item is geared towards your current tradeskills level. At higher tradeskills levels you get very good cash for these. You get ZERO experience.<br>
<br>
You can only do a set number of tasks per level (at higher levels I believe you will not be given tasks anymore). I'm not sure of the exact number. Consignments do COUNT towards your total number of tasks per level, but you will not be prevented from getting more consignments once you reach your maximum per level. So if you plan to do XP tasks and tradeskills, do your XP tasks first, then switch to consignments.<br>
<br>
There are 4 types of NPC's to give out tasks. A Kill Task giver, a Fedex Task giver, your tradeskills Master, and then  NPC's without tasks.<br>
<br>
By default almost ALL NPC merchants give out Fedex Tasks. Named Sentinels and certain named NPC's give out Kill Tasks. Your trademaster will give out Consignments. Very few NPC's give out no tasks (mainly unnamed guardians and sentinels).<br>
